    <subfield code="a">Polish-American poet, born and educated in Detroit, Michigan.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The collection consists of Pacosz's family records, correspondence, personal diaries, copies of her published work, including serial publications and anthologies containing her poetry, CDs and DVDs with recordings of festivals and reading. The diaries are detailed glimpses into her thoughts, her life as a poet, her teaching, travels, and daily acitivities. Also included are hospital records of Pacosz's aunt Janina Pacosz who was sterilized for the reason of mental disability and Christina Pacosz's reflections on the subject.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="506" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The collection is open for research use.</subfield>
